Gloss: to splash around in the water
to raise a child, to grow vegetables

infix added to j-stem verbs, especially those related to motion, to form class 1 verbs with senses relating to causing the motion or transference of a thing
burri-j-ba (“to cross a body of water”) → burrijkunumba (“to take (some thing) across a body of water”)
wi-j-ba (“return, go back”) → wi-j-kunu-mba (“bring or take (something or someone) back”)
